“Joy.” He knew I hated his surprises, and I made sure he could see the level of distrust all over my face.
He opened the door and ushered me inside, but I found myself confused as I stepped onto the freshly cleaned carpet. The room was completely bare. All the bedroom furniture was gone, the windows bare of their curtains, and the walls were completely white.
“Damn, I thought there was going to be a tiger in here,” I said, sounding disappointed. “Do you want one?”
I turned excited. “For real?”
He chuckled before his face went serious again. “No. One baby tiger around here is enough. I can’t imagine having a full-grown adult as well.”
I raised a brow at him. Was … was that a fucking joke?
“Anyway, this empty space is your surprise because I’m going to let you redecorate it however you want.”
