He shrugged. “Yeah, paint it, expand it, turn it into a basketball court. I don’t care as long as you do something with it. There are a bunch of home magazines and catalogs in my office that you can go through and order whatever you need. Furniture, lights, electronics, art, a PlayStation, whatever. I’m giving you a blank canvas to turn into anything you want. Make it your own.”
