Tomorrow morning couldn’t come fast enough.




I spent the next two hours in Darren’s office looking through catalogs while listening to him make plans and strategize with Scott to take down the guy who organized our attack. I was actually surprised I was even privy to them, but it was educating getting to listen in on his thought process, how he assessed potential problems and how to resolve them, what to expect, who to look for, and what weapons they would need. I felt absolutely fucking stupid sitting there deciding on drapes while they discussed artillery.
