After checking the paint job of the room, I was satisfied with the way the colors looked in the lighting. I’d chosen a soft gray to complement a sort of mauve color that I thought meshed pretty well. I didn’t want anything too loud in this room. I needed something calming. A place where I could just

relax. As I returned to Darren’s room, the room that I now shared with him, it came to my attention I now had yet another set of eyes on me.
I didn’t know Darren’s reasons, but I knew Carla wasn’t here just to spy on me.


44.

