That immediately stunned me into silence.
I’d never even considered love as a factor in any of this. Why did a man who couldn’t concern himself with sympathy or guilt be so concerned with something as inconsequential as love? Not to mention it wasn’t as if he was trying that hard to win my affection in a way that would inspire real love. The end of our honeymoon had ensured that.
Especially now that I knew Jason was alive and had a plan.
